30/01/2009
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- A suspected al-Qaeda activist died on Thursday (January 29th) during a 10-minute shootout in Istanbul. Three people suspected of terrorist activities were arrested in the action. It began when a masked gang tried to rob a post office in one of Istanbul's districts. Eyewitnesses say when they encountered police, the gunmen opened fire immediately. One police officer was injured.
In other news Thursday, police seized 1.5 tonnes of hashish from a group of suspected supporters of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party in Diyarbakir. Most of the hashish was hidden in a minefield. Police also confiscated weapons and ammunition in the operation. (CNN Turk, AFP, Reuters - 29/01/09)
